PROBLEM STATEMENT
A telecom company wants to analyze its customer data to:

1. Identify trends in customer churn over time.
2. Detect customers at high risk of leaving.
3. Understand how churn affects revenue.
4. Provide insights for retention strategies (like targeted offers).

The company has data including customer demographics, usage, subscription plans, billing,
and churn status.

SOLUTION APPROACH

1. Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
o Handle missing values.
o Convert categorical columns to numeric if needed.
o Create features like tenure groups.

2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
o Churn trends over tenure, contract type, plan type.
o Visualize high-risk customer segments.
o Analyze revenue per churned vs active customers.

3. High-Risk Customer Identification
o Use churn probability scores via logistic regression or decision tree.
o Highlight customers with high monthly charges + short tenure + month-to-
month contract.

4. Retention Insights
o Identify segments with high churn probability.
o Suggest strategies: loyalty programs, plan upgrades, targeted offers.